 traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Celano","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Fiore, Guido, Osvaldo, Tullio, Vito, Antonio, Bernardo, Geno, Giuseppe, Leonardo, Marino, Mario, Nino, Orazio.","Italian: habitational name from a place called Celano, in L'Aquila province."],"variants":[{"name":"Celani","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Domenic, Dario, Gabriele, Matteo, Natale, Salvatore, Vincenzo.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Celano  ."]}]},{"name":"Ruggero","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>Roger</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Comte Ruggero di Celano was born about 1215, in Italy, his father, Comte Tomaso di Celano, was 34 and his mother, Contessa Iodetta di Molise, was 32. He married Contessa Maria di Aquino in 1249. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1280, at the age of 67, and was buried in Italy."},"et":{"ABT 1215–ABT 1280":"umbes 1215–umbes 1280","1215–1280":"1215–1280","1227–1283":"1227–1283","1253–1324":"1253–1324","1182–1252":"1182–1252","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1253":"1253","1252":"1252","ABT 1215":"umbes 1215","1185":"1185","1283":"1283","1182":"1182","1280":"1280","1249":"1249","1227":"1227","1215":"1215","1324":"1324","ABT 1280":"umbes 1280","about 1252":"umbes 1252","Italy":"Itaalia","Celano, L'Aquila, Abruzzo, Italy":"Celano, L'Aquila, Abruzzo, Itaalia"},"fi":{"ABT 1215–ABT 1280":"noin 1215–noin 1280","1215–1280":"1215–1280","1227–1283":"1227–1283","1253–1324":"1253–1324","1182–1252":"1182–1252","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1253":"1253","1252":"1252","ABT 1215":"noin 1215","1185":"1185","1283":"1283","1182":"1182","1280":"1280","1249":"1249","1227":"1227","1215":"1215","1324":"1324","ABT 1280":"noin 1280","about 1252":"noin 1252","Italy":"Italia","Celano, L'Aquila, Abruzzo, Italy":"Celano, L'Aquila, Abruzzo, Italia"},"fr":{"ABT 1215–ABT 1280":"environ 1215–environ 1280","1215–1280":"1215–1280","1227–1283":"1227–1283","1253–1324":"1253–1324","1182–1252":"1182–1252","1185–Female":"1185–Décédée","1253":"1253","1252":"1252","ABT 1215":"environ 1215","1185":"1185","1283":"12